The airspace at Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KLIA) will be closed from Tuesday, 27 Aug to Saturday, 31 Aug from 9.00 to 10.30 a.m. for Malaysia’s 62nd National Day rehearsals and celebration. More info: https://t.co/NIUU8mNm95

Staying true to our spirit of delivering the best of Malaysian Hospitality, our MH Rangers went to the ground to give our fellow colleagues the much needed help.
 
Let’s give a shout out to our true heroes! https://t.co/NPcxyd6pbg

With the network disruption at KLIA these past few days, which has affected check-in, boarding and baggage handling systems, it has been an extra challenge for the team as sorting of bags had to be done manually. https://t.co/VIm7Ip4gyZ

Baggage sorting is no easy feat.
 
Rain or shine, our baggage handling team works hard to ensure passengers’ baggage are properly loaded into the right aircraft. More than an average of 20,000 bags are processed daily out of Kuala Lumpur International Airport (KLIA). https://t.co/u061SVQicE
Your safety and security are our utmost priority and we will do our best to ensure seamless experience for your travel. https://t.co/tcJ1eoCH3q

We have deployed more than 300 Rangers since Thursday and more are around this weekend positioned across all touch points, ultimately to ensure minimal delays in flight departure and arrivals. https://t.co/ms6KbegABM
